  <title>Enable multi-organisation unit data
    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170126T181827+0100" comment="Add screen shot"?>entry<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <para>
    <screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata width="80%" align="center"
            fileref="resources/images/data_entry/data_entry_multiple_org_unit.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
  </para>
  <para>It can be useful to enter data for multiple organisation units in the same data entry form,
    for instance if there are few data elements in the form and a huge number of organisation units
    in the hierarchy. In that case, you can enable multi-organisation unit data entry.</para>
  <para>
    <note>
      <para>Multi-organisation unit data entry only works for
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170126T181800+0100" comment="Still correct?"?>section<?oxy_comment_end?>
        forms.</para>
    </note>
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">System Settings</emphasis> app.</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Enable multi-organisation unit forms</emphasis>.</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Data Entry</emphasis> app, select the organisation unit
        immediately above the organisation unit you want to enter data for in the organisation unit
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170126T182148+0100" comment="Do you also need to select a data set?"?>hierarchy<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
      <para>Data elements will appear as columns and organisation units as rows in the form.</para>
      <para>
        <note>
          <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170126T182039+0100" comment="Is this still correct and relevant?"?>
          <para>The data entry forms should still be assigned to the facilities that you actually
            enter data for, that is the organisation units now appearing in the form.</para>
          <?oxy_comment_end?>
        </note>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</section>
